President Biden has directed his administration to ensure the safety and availability of infant formula during the Abbott Nutrition voluntary recall. The President spoke with retailers and manufacturers, including the CEOs of Walmart, Target, Reckitt, and Gerber, to urge them to do more to help families purchase infant formula. He discussed efforts to increase production and asked for other ways the administration can assist. The President also announced steps to expedite the availability of infant formula, including cutting red tape, cracking down on price gouging, and increasing imports. The administration will continue to monitor the situation and support efforts to increase production and distribution. The President also marked the tragic milestone of 1 million lives lost to COVID-19 in the United States and emphasized the urgency of the crisis. He called on Congress to take action to fight COVID-19 at home and abroad.